oration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">google</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read Larry Page Sounds Very Sick and Bad" href="http://gizmodo.com/5978144/larry-page-sounds-very-sick-and-bad"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read Larry Page Sounds Very Sick and Bad" alt="Click here to read Larry Page Sounds Very Sick and Bad" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18cbiv30zi4fojpg/original.jpg"><span></span> </a></div> </div> <!-- videoId: v/48cd8812 --><!-- /videoId: v/48cd8812 --> Internet deity and Google co-founder Larry Page was just speaking live to investors for Google's quarterly earnings call, and he sounds horrible. What the hell is going on here? <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5978144/larry-page-sounds-very-sick-and-bad" title="Click here to read more about Larry Page Sounds Very Sick and Bad">More&nbsp;&raquo;</a> <br><img width="1" height="1" src="http://gizmodo.feedsportal.com/c/34976/f/647164/s/27cad88f/mf.gif" border="0"><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884793302/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad88f/kg/342/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884793302/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad88f/kg/342/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151884793302/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad88f/kg/342/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/Mm1J1aT83X8" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"d6f3613bb90ce61c42ed796ba279cd03";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:48:"iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks";s:4:"link";s:102:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/BKmvQiQ4GRg/ios-ice-cubes-because-iphones-cant-chill-drinks";s:6:"author";s:11:"Leslie Horn";s:4:"date";i:1358892000;s:7:"content";s:1987:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks" href="http://gizmodo.com/daily-desired/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">dailydesired</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks" href="http://gizmodo.com/5978105/ios-ice-cubes-because-iphones-cant-chill-drinks"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks" alt="Click here to read iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18cbahn326urcjpg/xlarge.jpg"></a></div> </div> Dropping your iPhone in the drink is always an unfortunate thing but if you drop <a href="http://store.gama-go.com/iCubes-Ice-Cube-tray-p/ea1318.htm">Gamago's iOS icon ice cubes</a> ($8) in your glass, you'll be the opposite of sad because your drink will be cold and your phone safe. Ice bath, good. Damaged phone rice bath, bad. <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5978105/ios-ice-cubes-because-iphones-cant-chill-drinks" title="Click here to read more about iOS Ice Cubes Because iPhones Can't Chill Drinks">More&nbsp;&raquo;</a> <br><img width="1" height="1" src="http://gizmodo.feedsportal.com/c/34976/f/647164/s/27cad6a4/mf.gif" border="0"><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884793060/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad6a4/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884793060/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad6a4/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151884793060/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/27cad6a4/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/BKmvQiQ4GRg" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"8e27ab562350d879a50ba0647e477ade";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:85:"AMD earnings continue decline with $1.16 billion in Q4 revenue, $5.42 billion in 2012";s:4:"link";s:56:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/amd-q4-2012-earnings/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Zach Honig";s:4:"date";i:1358891100;s:7:"content";s:1995:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/amd-q4-2012-earnings/"><img alt="" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2012/10/amd-trinity-a10.jpeg"></a></p><p> We can't say AMD's declining momentum <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/10/10/gartner-and-idc-pc-shipments-tumbled-over-8-percent-in-q3/">was unexpected</a>, but these results don't necessarily have us excited about the future, nonetheless. For Q4, the company posted revenue of $1.16 billion, which is a 32-percent drop from the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/01/24/amd-q4-2011-earnings/">same period in 2011</a>, netting a loss of 63 cents per share. For 2012 as a whole, the company's revenue rang in at $5.42 billion -- a 17-percent fall from the previous year, and a $1.60 loss per share. President Rory Read references evolution and diversification when discussing outlook, but it's clear that the company needs to make some major adjustments before it can return to profitability. Let's hope that AMD's <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/10/amd-temash-reference-laptop-hands-on/">2013 lineup</a>, including the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/07/amd-temash-kabini-richland-kaveri-apu/">Temash and Kabini APUs</a>, help to turn this company around. You'll find full Q4 and 2012 earnings in the PDF at the source link below.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/desktops/" rel="tag">Desktops</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/amd/" rel="tag">AMD</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/22/amd-q4-2012-earnings/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/01/22/on-weak-pc-market-amd-hits-revenue-targets-with-1-16-for-q4-but-loses-0-63-per-share">The Next Web</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://phx.corporate-ir.net/External.File?item=UGFyZW50SUQ9MTY4NzE3fENoaWxkSUQ9LTF8VHlwZT0z&amp;t=1">AMD (PDF)</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:8:"Engadget";}s:32:"7af0716817074fe55e38513a3e1c71fc";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:66:"You Can Drive This RC Duster Over Every Dirty Surface In Your Home";s:4:"link";s:121:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/z6ToXKi349k/you-can-drive-this-rc-duster-over-every-dirty-surface-in-your-home";s:6:"author";s:16:"Andrew Liszewski";s:4:"date";i:1358890800;s:7:"content";s:2067:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read You Can Drive This RC Duster Over Every Dirty Surface In Your Home" href="http://gizmodo.com/toys/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">toys</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read You Can Drive This RC Duster Over Every Dirty Surface In Your Home" href="http://gizmodo.com/5978102/you-can-drive-this-rc-duster-over-every-dirty-surface-in-your-home"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read You Can Drive This RC Duster Over Every Dirty Surface In Your Home" alt="Click here to read You Can Drive This RC Duster Over Every Dirty Surface In Your Home" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18cb97frt640bjpg/xlarge.jpg"><span></span> </a></div> </div> The problem with robot vacuums like the Roomba is that they're only designed to deal with dirt on the floor. The rest of your house&mdash;from furniture, to counter tops, to shelves&mdash;is left for you to clean: a chore made considerably more awesome with this remote control 